Speaker 2: I did order some maybe two or three weeks ago, or maybe a month ago, and I'm assuming

Speaker 1: you put me on a renewal, but I do not want to be on a renewal.

Speaker 2: I would like to live, okay?

Speaker 1: What's your zip code?

Speaker 2: 52246.

Speaker 1: What's your name?

Speaker 2: My last name is Clemens, C-L-E-M-O-N-S.

Speaker 2: You don't have to get it this way?

Speaker 1: That's right.

Speaker 2: I do not want it to be automatically renewed.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All you have to do is set this up, and it would have came out that way.

Speaker 1: I can do that for you now.

Speaker 2: Is that what you're looking for?

Speaker 1: Yes, please.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Well, we will do that for you now.

Speaker 2: So basically, we'll just keep your prescription open for the next five months, and you'll

Speaker 1: have to call us for your next order.

Speaker 2: I'll have to call you.

Speaker 1: Can I get a confirmation of that?

Speaker 2: No, just a verbal confirmation.

Speaker 1: I just changed that for you now.

Speaker 2: So you're going to have to call us for your next one.

Speaker 1: You won't.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: We're keeping the prescription open, and you're going to have to call for your next order.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.
